The ackwards package as a whole is released under the MIT License (see the
DESCRIPTION "License" field and the LICENSE file).

The following bundled files are licensed separately:

  data/amh_cor.rda
  tests/testthat/fixtures/forbes2023_amh.rds

    data/amh_cor.rda is the exported `amh_cor` dataset: the 155-variable
    "Assessing Mental Health" (AMH) Spearman correlation matrix from Forbes
    (2023, below). tests/testthat/fixtures/forbes2023_amh.rds holds the
    expected between-level correlations and loading congruences derived from
    that same matrix (details below). Both are the AMH correlation matrix from:

      Forbes, M. K. (2023). Improving hierarchical models of individual
      differences: An extension of Goldberg's bass-ackward method.
      Psychological Methods. https://doi.org/10.1037/met0000546

    Source: OSF project https://osf.io/pcwm8/ (file corSpearman_AMH.csv,
    guid s9bjz). The matrix is redistributed here under its original license,

      Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY 4.0)
      https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

    with attribution to M. K. Forbes as above. The expected between-level
    correlations and loading congruences in forbes2023_amh.rds were computed
    from that matrix using Forbes's own reference implementation
    ("ExtendedBassAckwards functions with annotation.R", guid 7jfkw, same OSF
    project and license). See data-raw/amh_cor.R, which regenerates both files
    from a single md5-pinned download, for provenance.
